  stimulus_text = 'In the early 1960s, American singer-songwriter Bob Dylan released a series of albums that revolutionized the way popular music was made and consumed.  Dylan’s music, which embraced a folk-rock sound and often addressed social and political issues, helped to define the counterculture movement of the time.  What are the most likely reasons that these albums were so influential?',
